# Alogyan — REST & GraphQL API Design

> Base URL: `https://api.alogyan.com/v1`  
> GraphQL: `https://api.alogyan.com/graphql`  
> All endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <Firebase ID Token>` unless marked **[PUBLIC]**

---

## 1. Authentication & Authorization

### Authentication Flow

```
Client                    Firebase Auth           API Backend
  │                           │                       │
  │── signIn (email/phone) ──▶│                       │
  │◀──── ID Token ────────────│                       │
  │                           │                       │
  │── GET /students ─────────────────────────────────▶│
  │   Authorization: Bearer <idToken>                  │
  │                           │                       │
  │                           │◀── verifyIdToken() ───│
  │                           │                       │
  │                           │──── { uid, claims } ──▶│
  │                           │                       │
  │◀──────────── 200 JSON ────────────────────────────│
```

### Firebase Custom Claims (Role System)

```json
{
  "role": "teacher",        // "teacher" | "admin" | "student"
  "teacherId": "T_xyz123",  // present for teacher role
  "plan": "pro"             // "free" | "pro"
}
```

### Role-Based Access Matrix

| Resource | Teacher (own data) | Admin | Student |
|---|---|---|---|
| Own profile | R/W | R/W | — |
| Students | R/W | R | R (self only) |
| Batches | R/W | R | R (enrolled) |
| Attendance | R/W | R | R (own) |
| Fees | R/W | R | R (own) |
| Notes | R/W | R | R (batch) |
| Announcements | R/W | R | R |
| Reports | R | R | — |
| Admin panel | — | R/W | — |

> **Multi-tenant rule**: Every query in the backend appends `WHERE teacherId = token.teacherId`. A teacher can never read another teacher's data.

---

## 2. Standard Envelope

### Success Response

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { ... },
  "meta": {
    "page": 1,
    "pageSize": 20,
    "total": 150,
    "totalPages": 8
  },
  "timestamp": "2026-03-21T18:07:00.000Z"
}
```

### Error Response

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "STUDENT_NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "Student with ID s_abc123 not found",
    "details": { "id": "s_abc123" }
  },
  "timestamp": "2026-03-21T18:07:00.000Z"
}
```

### HTTP Status Codes

| Situation | Code |
|---|---|
| Success with body | `200 OK` |
| Created resource | `201 Created` |
| Success, no body | `204 No Content` |
| Bad input / validation | `400 Bad Request` |
| Missing / invalid token | `401 Unauthorized` |
| Valid token, no permission | `403 Forbidden` |
| Resource not found | `404 Not Found` |
| Conflict (duplicate) | `409 Conflict` |
| Rate limit exceeded | `429 Too Many Requests` |
| Server error | `500 Internal Server Error` |

### Standard Error Codes

```
AUTH_TOKEN_MISSING          AUTH_TOKEN_EXPIRED          AUTH_TOKEN_INVALID
FORBIDDEN_RESOURCE          STUDENT_NOT_FOUND           BATCH_NOT_FOUND
ATTENDANCE_NOT_FOUND        FEE_RECORD_NOT_FOUND        NOTE_NOT_FOUND
ANNOUNCEMENT_NOT_FOUND      DUPLICATE_ENROLLMENT        SEAT_LIMIT_REACHED
FEE_ALREADY_GENERATED       INVALID_DATE_RANGE          VALIDATION_ERROR
RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED         INTERNAL_ERROR
```

### Pagination Query Params

```
?page=1&pageSize=20&sortBy=createdAt&sortOrder=desc
```

